<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="415" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,1052,1287]" pageId="14" pageNumber="415">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,1052,1078]" pageId="14" pageNumber="415">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="McLachlan" authorityYear="1898" box="[281,384,1052,1078]" class="Insecta" family="Ascalaphidae" genus="Bubopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="415" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[281,384,1052,1078]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="415">Bubopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be characterized by the presence of long male ectoprocts (equal to the length of last four abdominal segments taken together) with long median branch directed downward (
<bibRefCitation author="Yang, M. X. &amp; Wang, X. L. &amp; Sun, M. X." box="[1093,1287,1087,1113]" pageId="14" pageNumber="415" pagination="7451" refId="ref29188" refString="Yang, M. X., Wang, X. L. &amp; Sun, M. X. (2016) Two newly recorded genera and species of owlflies (Neuroptera: Ascalaphidae) from China. Biodiversity Data Journal, 4, e 7451. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / BDJ. 4. e 7451" type="journal article" year="2016">
Yang 
<emphasis box="[1161,1219,1087,1113]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="415">et al.</emphasis>
2016
</bibRefCitation>
: figs 10–13). Moreover, it differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="Lefebvre" authorityName="Lefebvre" authorityYear="1842" box="[438,741,1121,1147]" class="Insecta" family="Ascalaphidae" genus="Deleproctophylla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="415" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[438,633,1121,1147]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="415">Deleproctophylla</emphasis>
Lefèbvre
</taxonomicName>
by the hyaline, immaculate wings.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="415" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,1052,1287]" pageId="14" pageNumber="415">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,262,1156,1182]" pageId="14" pageNumber="415">Note.</emphasis>
In Asia, this genus is represented by five species and one subspecies (
<bibRefCitation author="Sziraki, G." box="[1067,1216,1156,1182]" pageId="14" pageNumber="415" pagination="57 - 72" refId="ref28571" refString="Sziraki, G. (1998) An annotated checklist of the Ascalaphidae species known from Asia and from the Pacific Islands. Folia Entomologica Hungarica, 59, 57 - 72. [BotN ref  9362]" type="journal article" year="1998">Sziráki 1998</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Sziraki, G." box="[1229,1290,1156,1182]" pageId="14" pageNumber="415" refId="ref28610" refString="Sziraki, G. (2000) Data to the knowledge of the Asian Ascalaphidae (Neuroptera), with description of a new subspecies. Folia Entomologica Hungarica Rovartania Kozlemenyek, 87 - 93. [BotN ref  9872]" type="journal volume" year="2000">2000</bibRefCitation>
). It currently includes a single species in 
<collectingCountry box="[461,559,1191,1217]" name="Pakistan" pageId="14" pageNumber="415">Pakistan</collectingCountry>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="van der Weele, 1909" authorityName="van der Weele" authorityYear="1909" box="[570,996,1191,1217]" class="Insecta" family="Ascalaphidae" genus="Bubopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="415" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tancrei">
<emphasis box="[570,758,1191,1217]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="415">Bubopsis tancrei</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="van der Weele, H. W." box="[765,996,1191,1217]" pageId="14" pageNumber="415" pagination="1 - 326" refId="ref29095" refString="van der Weele, H. W. (1909) Ascalaphiden. Collections Zoologiques du Baron Edm. de Selys Longchamps, Catalogue Systematique et Descriptif, 8, 1 - 326. [BotN ref  420]" type="journal article" year="1909">van der Weele, 1909</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, which was listed as present among the Neuropterida in the National Museums of Scotland (
<bibRefCitation author="Whittington, A. E." box="[737,942,1225,1251]" pageId="14" pageNumber="415" pagination="371 - 387" refId="ref29063" refString="Whittington, A. E. (2002) Resources in Scottish Neuropterology. Acta Zoologica Academiae Scientiarum Hungaricae, 48, 371 - 387. [BotN ref  10317]" type="journal article" year="2002">Whittington 2002</bibRefCitation>
). Until now, there is no detailed information available about the exact locality of this species in 
<collectingCountry box="[721,820,1260,1286]" name="Pakistan" pageId="14" pageNumber="415">Pakistan</collectingCountry>
. No new specimens were recorded in this study.
</paragraph>
